      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior pedicle screw FEA validation studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of six prior independent FEA validation studies for pedicle screw constructs under compression-bending loading (Rohlmann 2001, Goel 2003, Vadapalli 2006, Xu 2009, Ayturk 2011, Patel 2014). Across these studies, FEA models consistently predicted construct stiffness within 8% of experimental values and yield force within 12%. This synthesis provides strong contextual support that the modeling methodology is well-established and that the acceptance bounds selected for COU1 are conservative relative to the broader literature. The synthesis was assembled by the DePuy Synthes computational team as a supporting evidence document for the FDA submission package."
    }
