  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-noncannulated-decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/depuy-synthes-vv-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3 due to the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol; this shortfall is accepted given regulatory standardization of the test method and the conservative nature of the acceptance bounds. Quantitative validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs) are satisfied. The credibility evidence package, including the prior literature synthesis, supports an overall medium assurance level consistent with the medium model risk and medium decision consequence. Decision: Accepted.",
